u}| \leq 10^{-6}$, respectively, in the $\mu 
u$SSM. In the top left panel, the values in the border between regions are labeled, and for the rest of the panels the labeling is the same. If the same point can be probed in both panels, a double-line signal could be measured. The red region corresponds to points disfavored be tested by e-ASTROGAM. In the left panels, the black solid lines show different values of $	au_{	ilde{a}} \simeq \Gamma^{-1}(	ilde{a}ightarrow \psi_{3/2} \, a)$ between $10^5$ and $10^{21}$ s. All the points shown satisfy $\Omega_{3/2}h^2+\Omega_{	ilde{a}}h^2$ equal to $\Omega_{cdm}^{	ext{Planck}}h^2$ at recombination era in agreement with Planck observations, as well as DDM constraints for $f_{ddm}^{	ext{DR}}$.

